The integrated contingency plan is updated when necessary based on modifications made to the NOVA Chemicals' Beaver Valley plant  processes to ensure appropriate emergency response plans exist.



Plans to Improve Safety



The NOVA Chemicals' Beaver Valley plant as a Responsible Care facility is committed to continuously looking for new ways to improve plant safety.  Some examples are:  



1.    Assessing control instruments to assure that the most reliable and effective controls are used; 

2.    Conducting and reviewing hazard assessments; 

3.    Controlling plant access; 

4.    Observing job tasks to identify and correct unsafe behaviors in the work environment; 

5.    Evaluating product handling and shipping procedures. 



The NOVA Chemicals' Beaver Valley plant has communicated its chemical safety and accident prevention program and risk management information to employees and community leaders.



For additional information, please call Nova Chemicals at 1.866.ASK.NOVA or access the Nova Chemicals, Inc. website at www.novachem.com.
